des: "Hi, my name is Molly. I am 13 years old and I love this recipe my mom makes every once in awhile.  This makes a good family meal side dish.  It is also very easy to make ! So, please have fun with this recipe."
ins:
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).
In a 1 1/2 quart casserole combine broken spaghetti, whole kernel corn, cheese, cream-style corn and margarine.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until spaghetti is cooked.
